            <div id="htmlcaption-0" class="nivo-html-caption">
            <span class="title">Recycling</span><br />
            <span class="content">All the materials used in beverage cartons are recyclable. In 2017, 48% of beverage cartons in EU-28 were recycled. </span>
        </div>
                <div id="htmlcaption-1" class="nivo-html-caption">
            <span class="title">Forestry</span><br />
            <span class="content">100% of the paperboard produced in Europe for the manufacturing of beverage cartons comes from paper mills that have an FSC certified chain-of-custody in place.</span>
        </div>
                <div id="htmlcaption-2" class="nivo-html-caption">
            <span class="title">Environmental Footprint</span><br />
            <span class="content">Beverage cartons have the lowest carbon footprint in their core categories of milk and fruit juice packaging.</span>
        </div>
                <div id="htmlcaption-3" class="nivo-html-caption">
            <span class="title">Resource Efficiency</span><br />
            <span class="content">The beverage carton industry now produces 40% more cartons with the same amount of wood fibres as 20 years ago.</span>
